- Replace neo-tree with Oil.nvim
- Replace fzf-lua with snacks lists
- Use Neovim native completion instead of blink-cmp
- 
  Disable Semantic Tokens: LSPs often send "color info" on every keystroke.[1] It’s redundant if you have Treesitter.[1]
 code
 Lua
 -- Inside your LSP on_attach function
 ```
 on_attach = function(client, bufnr)
   client.server_capabilities.semanticTokensProvider = nil
 end
 ```


- redo Treesitter

- reduce the timout length vim.opt.timeoutlen = 300 -- Default is 1000ms.

- Disable Built-in Bloat: Neovim loads old plugins like netrw and tutor by default.[1] Kill them in your init.lua:
code
Lua
local builtins = {
  "netrw", "netrwPlugin", "netrwSettings", "netrwFileHandlers",
  "gzip", "zip", "zipPlugin", "tar", "tarPlugin",
  "getscript", "getscriptPlugin", "vimball", "vimballPlugin",
  "2html_plugin", "logipat", "rrhelper", "spellfile_plugin", "matchit"
}
for _, plugin in ipairs(builtins) do
  vim.g["loaded_" .. plugin] = 1
end


